description:
&lt;p&gt;In this role you’ll be working within our strong Medicines Management team to help safely supply and administer medicines to patients. You’ll also help deliver minor ailments services, serve as a key point of advice to patients in regards to medicines management, help manage the prison’s medicine supplies, and help with medicines reconciliation and supporting patients with their prescription pathways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through all of this, you’ll serve as a vital point of contact for patients in HMP Eastwood Park – you’ll empower the prison’s population to understand their medicines better and critically manage their own self-care in regards to their long-term health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn’t a job for everyone. You’ll need to be non-judgemental, resilient, and dedicated. In return you’ll be rewarded through being part of a wider healthcare team that delivers care beyond health - in helping educate your patients to make better life choices, in turn reducing the likelihood of reoffending. This is a real opportunity to gain unique experience and to develop your Pharmacy career to the next level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charlotte Gawenda, Medicines Management Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;charlotte.gawenda@nhs.net  Telephone number01454 382303&lt;/p&gt;
